    //Javi text
    "Javi_lovedgift": "That's the good stuff.",
    "Javi_likedgift": "Not bad, @.",
    "Javi_dislikedgift": "What were you thinking?",
    "Javi_hatedgift": "Is this a bad joke?",
    "Javi_neutralgift": "I'll give it some use.",
    //dialogue
    "Dialogue.Clearance":"This weather is unbearable...Here's perfect for relaxing.#$b#It's got good shade.",
    "Dialogue.GingerIsland":"This island is like a lighting rod for pirates. I wonder why.",
    "Dialogue.Trader": "For an island, there's not many people to trade with.",
    "Dialogue.HiddenBeach":"Not many people know of this beach.#$b#It's nice to come 'ere once in a while.",
    "Dialogue.Rain": "The rain...#$b#It reminds me of the ocean.",
    "Dialogue.BlueDiscus":"Have you ever eaten blue discus?#$b#No?",
    "Dialogue.Dwarves":"What? Dwarves? Those are just fairytales.",
    "Dialogue.Farm":"How's life in the farm, @?",
    "Dialogue.Crops":"How are those crops coming along?",
    "Dialogue.OtherIslands":"Have you visited the other islands? You should sometime.",
    "Dialogue.Fishing":"I can't get tired of fish. You can cook them in many ways.#$b#You can fry them, put them in a stew...",
    //post-8h
    "Dialogue.Alone": "If it gets lonely in the island? Well...#$b#Yes, but I like the peace.",
    "Dialogue.Volcano": "The volcano? I don't know much.#$b#I prefer fishing.",
    "Dialogue.Volcano2": "Sometimes, sprites escape from the volcano.#$b#I don't like using that sword, but if it has to be done...$4#$e#Where I got the sword from?#$b#Don't worry about it.",
    "Dialogue.Caldera": "There's a forge atop the volcano?#$b#That's weird.",
    "Dialogue.Leo": "If I know Leo? Of course.#$b#That kid's good with parrots. But they flee from me.",
    "Dialogue.Journal": "That journal was never meant to be seen.#$b#Sometimes, thoughts plague my head...$2#$b#And writing helps.",
    "Dialogue.Gender": "Birdie was confused.#$b#She remembered a quartermaster, but thought it was a man.#$b#Everyone else did.$1#$e#Not that I mind.",
    "Dialogue.Softspot": "There was a rumour in our ship. 'The quartermaster has a soft spot for ladies'.#$b#...#$b#It was true.$7",
    "Dialogue.Haircut": "Why I don't cut my hair now?#$b#I like how it looks.",
    "Dialogue.LeoGone1": "I keep forgetting Leo is in the valley and checking in on him.",
    "Dialogue.LeoGone2": "How is he doing, @?",
    "Dialogue.LeoGone3": "I miss the kid, but it's better this way.",
    "Dialogue.Parrot":"We used to have a chicken in the ship.#$b#I wonder what happened to it.",
    "Dialogue.Parrot2":"Asides from a chicken, we had a cow one time.#$b#What? We had to eat somehow.$5",
    "Dialogue.Boredom":"Sometimes, we'd spend days without seeing a ship.#$b#We had our own ways to combat boredom.#$b#Playing cards, dice, dividing the loot...$6",
    "Dialogue.Boredom2":"When we had nothing else to do, some played instruments or sang.#$b#One lad was awful at singing, but he put his whole heart in it.",
    "Dialogue.Quartermaster":"Remember, @. A quartermaster's duty is to the crew, not the captain.",
    "Dialogue.HisFin":"I never understood why the cap'n took me under his fin.#$b#I was but a newbie.#$b#Nowadays, I think he saw potential in me.",
    "Dialogue.Before":"Had you asked in my childhood, I'm not sure what I'd have said about pirates.#$b#My father taught me to see them as a menace.#$e#Look where I ended up, though.",
    "Dialogue.Sailor":"You know, I wanted to be a sailor as a kid.#$b#Funny how things end up.",
    "Dialogue.Gender2":"Why I changed my gender when I joined the pirates?#$b#Well, it was easier that way. Women are rarely allowed in these places.#$e#Not that I didn't have fun doing it.",
    "Dialogue.Crew":"Some days I miss the crew. I wonder if anyone else survived that night.",
    "Dialogue.Crew2":"I don't think the crew were happy at their cap'n taking a young pirate under tutoring.#$b#But I digress.#$b#Most ships teach their newbies, not my fault we didn't have that yet.",
    "Dialogue.Rumours":"What do you mean whether I was \"A swindler or an ex navy member\"?#$b#@, where in the world are ye hearin' these things?$9",
    //post-12h
    "Dialogue.Mon_12h":"My childhood?#$b#I don't like talkin' about my life before the ship.",
    "Dialogue.Tue_12h":"Why piracy 'boomed'?#$b#Well, because it was profitable. That's why.",
    "Dialogue.Wed_12h":"You know, most people have a warped view about piracy.#$b#It's quite different from what you might hear or see in popular culture.",
    "Dialogue.Thu_12h":"Hey @. How's the farmer life treating you?",
    "Dialogue.Sat_12h":"What, you want to know why women were rarely allowed in pirate ships?#$b#It has to do with them being seen as bad luck and fears of the pirates fighting over them.",
    "Dialogue.Sun_12h":"Pirates have their own code, you know.#$b#It's designed to keep order aboard the ship, avoid dissension or mutinies, and ensure the crews' loyalty.",
    //gifting
    "Gift.tackle":"Nice. I was in need of new tackle.",
    "Gift.gem":"What do you even do with these?",
    "Gift.mineral":"What's this for?",
    "Gift.fish":"Nice. I'll use this for dinner.",
    "Gift.meat":"Where'd you get this, @? What a treat!",
    "Gift.curiosity_lure":"A curiosity lure? I've never seen one.",
    "Gift.truffle_oil":"Truffle oil? How gourmet.",
    "Gift.honey":"Is this from your farm? Thanks, @.",
    //gifting - post 8h event
    "Gift.gemOrMineral":"Thanks @, but I'm not a pirate anymore. I got no use for these.",

    "LovedMovie.Before":"They still make these movies?",
    "LovedMovie.During.Script":"Javi is glued to the screen...",
    "LovedMovie.During":"These actors know what they're doing.",
    "LovedMovie.After":"That was great! It brought back memories...$h",
    "LikedMovie.Before":"I'm willing to give it a go.",
    "LikedMovie.After":"Heh, that wasn't too bad. Thanks for inviting me.",
    "NormalMovie.Before":"You like these movies?",
    "NormalMovie.After":"That's new... It was OK.",
    "DislikedMovie.Before":"Hmph... I don't get it.",
    "DislikedMovie.During.Script":"It seems Javi is snoring...",
    "DislikedMovie.After":"That was... boring.",

    /* Journal entries */

    //format: journal.page.paragraph
    //it's meant to help get a little more context, since the other (unlisted) pages use event text.
    
    // DON'T EDIT "\n\n", it's a line break for the journal. Everything else can be edited just fine
    "Journal.5":"...Then, I had to make a choice to save my life. I saw in piracy my escape. I joined a pirate ship under another identity.\n\nIn my childhood I loved the sea, having sailed with my father. But... I never wanted it to be like this.\n\nWas life laughing in my face?",
    "Journal.6": "It was hard to survive in that ship. Everyone fought for control.\n\nYou were on your own.\n\n...\n\nI barely survived my first fight.",
    "Journal.7": "Then, I met him.\n\n\"I told you. No one dies in their first battle.\"\n\nBack then, I didn't understand why he did it.\n\nBut the captain took me under his fin.",
    "Journal.8":"As I spent time in the ship, I learned to fight.\n\nHadn't it been for that man, I'd been lost.\n\nKeeping track of the supplies, handling pirates' disputes...\n\nWith time, I learned the ways of a pirate.",
    "Journal.9":"I could handle myself on my own.\n\nI even showed the ropes to the rookies, just like how they'd done with me.\n\nBy that time, the crew trusted me to keep the captain in check. And him, to get them to listen. If a fight broke out, I was to be called.",
    "Journal.10":"Sometimes we saw no ships for days, so we'd gamble and play cards to kill time.\n\nIn those nights, I'd join the crew's antics.\n\nWe had no reason to go back to land.", 
    "Journal.12B":"They were known for catching pirates.\n\nWe weren't going to give in so easily. And a fight began.", 
    "Journal.13":"I was cornered during the battle. I knew I'd die there. But...the blow never came. \n\nWhen I opened my eyes, I saw the captain in front of me.\n\nI was used to bloodshed, but for some reason I froze. I couldn't speak.",
    "Journal.16C":"\"If you don't care for yourself, no one will.\" That's what my father used to tell me. So why did he..?",
    "Journal.17C":"I didn't know why I felt so heavy. But after all these years...I know now.",
    "Journal.19A":"A few years had passed. I learned that Birdie, the pirate's widow, lives here. She's searching for her husband.",
    "Journal.19B":"But I can't bring myself to tell her...",
    "Journal.21A":"A shipwreck happened. Only a child survived.",
    "Journal.21B":"At first I thought he'd stay until he recovered, and then be on his own. But looking as he rested, I remembered my childhood...",
    "Journal.21C":"I don't know if it was the guilt of everything else, but I took him in.",
    "Journal.22A":"I've never had a touch for caring for children...or the intention to.",
    "Journal.22B":"He's been befriending the parrots. The kid says they speak to him about a \"hut\" in the forest.",
    "Journal.23":"I don't know if I believe that, but I'll play along. In the best case, we find him a safer place. I can just bring him food there.",
    "Journal.25A":"I feel like someone's been looking through my things. I don't remember storing the journal away.",
    "Journal.25B":"But I've never told anyone of this.",
    "Journal.25C":"Is my memory failing?",
    "Journal.27":"So there was someone going through my things. {{player}}, you...",
    "Journal.29A.badend":"In the end...I couldn't tell her.",
    "Journal.29B.badend":"The dreams of that ship still haunt me, but...this is for the best. It's better if she goes on without knowing.",
    "Journal.29C.badend":"I wonder what would've happened if I told her...",
    "Journal.29A.goodend":"I've visited Birdie a few times after that. She's begun accepting things.",
    "Journal.29B.goodend":"We talk about him too. What he did at sea, our feats...I think it helps her to have someone to let it out. It's helped me too. I still have nightmares, but less than before.",
    "Journal.29C.goodend":"All of this 'cause someone read my journal.",
    
